Did you have the best time yesterday?
-
I certainly did and I haven‚Äôt woken up feeling like I‚Äôve done anything wrong.
-
A few years ago this wouldn‚Äôt have been the case, I would have been up and in the mirror pulling at my tummy.
-
Being pretty dam mean to myself and feeling very regretful about enjoying the indulgences of Christmas Day.
-
If this is you I want you to stop taking some deep breaths and let go of the anger, guilt and shame BECAUSE YOU HAVE DONE NOTHING WRONG.
-
And the best thing if you‚Äôre struggling with these feelings today is to stay out of your own head so grab a pen and paper and get head emptying.
-
Write down all of the conversations in your mind that are tormenting you and not allowing you to just think back to yesterday as a day of good memories.
-
The voices that are trash talking you and standing in your way of you getting on with your day getting back to a level of ‚Äúnormality‚Äù with your daily eating and moving habits.
-
Once you‚Äôve mind cleared get on with your day being your awesome self and focusing on doing things that make you feel good.
-
Have an amazing day I‚Äôm off for a walk and might do a quickie yoga sesh later what you up to?

5 years ago I sat on the edge of the sofa staring at the big box of chocolates.

I wanted one but I didn‚Äôt know the calories. I googled, I looked on my fitness pal but nothing was definite enough to settle my mind.

I sat in torment for half an hour then decided I was going in.

I picked out 2 penguins & ate them, it tasted so good, for a min I felt ok, but then it started.
-
‚Äùyou didn‚Äôt the calories‚Äù ‚Äúgo look in the mirror you got fat‚Äù ‚Äúyou might as well eat the whole box.‚Äù I went into panic I didn‚Äôt want to binge & deal with feeling sick & mind fogged so I had to distract myself & I needed to burn calories so I grabbed my trainers & went for a run.

I remember thinking ‚Äúwell you didn‚Äôt binge this time but you still ate bad food‚Äù felt as guilty & stressed as I did after a full jar of Nutella & cereal binge.

I had competed 2months ago in another attempt to try & feel happy & like I was good enough.

After months of restrictive dieting, I was struggling to regain any kind of normality around my relationship with food,

Food was no longer just food I saw it only as calories & they all had the potential to make me fat.

Food had become my number one enemy.

I lived in a tormented headspace of scarcity & deprivation which would often lead to binging & a constant feeling of guilt, shame & fear of getting fat so I would restrict and overtrain.

That Christmas to the outsider it looked like I had a joyous time but inside it was a different story.

After some deep delve work to change the relationship I have with myself this isn‚Äôt my life anymore, I am at peace with me so I can enjoy Christmas & all it has to offer without going OTT so I feel like crap & without feeling guilty.

My journey showed me that if you have a skew whiff relationship with food or alcohol then it‚Äôs never just about them.

They are just the bandaid to cope with what‚Äôs really going on.

And until you start feeling the feels you‚Äôre trying to avoid you can‚Äôt transform yourself & that's the truth.

"We are what we repeatedly do." This simple thought by Aristotle has helped me overcome procrastination, fear, laziness and plenty of the other self-limiting beliefs I've told myself to avoid the prospect of pain.

Want to be a writer? Are you writing? Want a better physique? Are you working out? Want better grades? Are you studying? Want to become an entrepreneur? Do you have a plan of action?

Success comes in small steps. That extra rep in the gym. That extra cold call. It's the little decisions that add up over time.

Final thought: In my college Art History class I had to come up with a 3-D art project that represented a famous artist. I decided I would recreate Andy Warhol's Campbell's soup can by duplicating it in the form of a cake.

I spent several hours grocery shopping, gathering ingredients, mixing batter, different colored icings, and eventually baking the cake. It wasn't until I began to put the finishing touches on it that people began to notice.

Classmates wanted to taste it. Neighboring professors came over to check it out.

Random students stopped me to chat.

All this made me realize one thing ‚Äî people don't care about the hard work; most of the time they won't even notice it, but they do recognize and respect the results.

Bake your cake. Do the work. And enjoy your success.

Self-care is about so much more than having your nails done it‚Äôs about being respectful and loving towards you, your body and your mind.
-
Is it always something you prioritise?
-
If you‚Äôre like my amazing client Angie I know how easy it is for self-care to get forgotten.
-
When life happens you struggle to remember your own needs which quite often leads to a negative self mindset.

And trying to reach a goal of any kind from a place of hate, disrespect and negativity towards yourself only leads you further away.

Because when you feel negative, frustrated or angry you make irrational decisions which result in you feeling worse which then whisks you off on the road to self-sabotage.

When Angie tosses herself on the back burner her old sabotaging behaviours reemerge & then she remembers that not looking after herself and just doing more is a HUGE false economy.
-
üëâüèªHer gym time is essential for her brain health
üëâüèª taking 10 minutes in nature makes her feel reconnected with herself and ignites her creativity.
üëâüèªspending time eating well helps her focus and perform better
üëèüèªpup time makes her feel calm, grateful & content.
-
The only way you can show up for you every day is if you are looking after yourself!

Yes, it also positively impacts everyone around you because you‚Äôre not constantly operating from a half-empty cup but that‚Äôs a side effect, not the main aim. You‚Äôre the priority.
-
Making yourself a priority may feel strange and may raise feelings of guilt but remember we are all equally important so don‚Äôt downplay your own.
-
Looking after you is nothing to feel guilty about you are 100% worth it, find things that make you feel good & do them!
-
Don't sit on the back burner in your life, you belong on the front ring¬† in full flame!
-

About a year ago I really started to grasp the importance of getting out of your own head as much as possible.
-
Growing up I was actually an avid ‚Äúdear diary‚Äù writer I rambled my child and teenage thoughts out onto the pages, talking to what I then thought of as my invisible friend what I know as my spirit guide!
-
But as with many things (playing musical instruments, singing, dancing), I totally abandoned it.
-
Little did I know that my younger self was a smart cookie because ‚ÄúDear Diary‚Äù was actually helping me to manage my mind and get out of my own head and my invisible friend was actually a huge source of peace for me!
-
Fast forward to now and I can put my hand on heart and say that these daily strategies are how I have managed to evolve so much over the last year, I have moved from just existing to actually living!
-
Don‚Äôt get me wrong I still have shaky times where I question my ability, my right to be doing the things I‚Äôm doing if I‚Äôm good enough and if I can truly have everything I want, I‚Äôm human and having those times are perfectly normal!
-
But rather than letting that become my whole existence and whisk me off on a path of self-sabotage I catch myself before it goes too far and get myself back to where I need to be.
-
For me they are powerful practices I will never abandon again! I observe & also live in my life! -
If you‚Äôve never tried any of these but would like to I suggest trying my 1-minute mindful morning which is a process I use with my coaching clients to ease them in to using some of these tools and also starting to build their morning routine.
-
Decide on 2-3 things you want to start doing then each morning you do them for 1 minute!
-
Then over time you can progress how you use them and start branching out and trying different things see what works best for you. ü•∞üíÉ

Friend when you break danced your way into this wonderful world you were destined to be something amazing!
-
Something that didn‚Äôt involve being defined by anything external!
-
Not the name of your diet, training program or the label Auntie Mabel put on you at age 6 which stuck!

In Mabel's defence, she probably didn't know being told you are the....(insert external label) would lead you to think it's not ok to behave in a way which doesn‚Äôt match your label.
üëâüèª so being the strong one has made you think it's wrong to be vulnerable.
üëâüèª ‚Äùyou‚Äôre just so independent ‚Äù means you never ask for help.
üëèüèª that being labelled as the overweight one has made you believe you can't be anything else.
-
Truth

Over the course of my life, I've let myself be defined by everything shown here.
-
üëâüèªI used to have a daily war with the scale number.
üëâüèªI spent a long time trying to ‚Äúfit in‚Äù so I experimented with various labels so changed how I acted, pretended I was interested in things, did lots of shit that didn‚Äôt make me happy!

It‚Äôs taken me a long time to accept that the only label I ever needed is one that reads ‚ÄúSarah Duff authentically me!‚Äù
-
Unapologetically weird & wonderful take me or leave me it matters not!
-
Not to mislead you in any way this just shift from filtered to unfiltered is shitballs hard work & it takes time!
-
But the process of moving into acceptance of yourself and letting go of letting the external stuff define your beautiful breakdancing self brings with it a total abundance of wing spreading freedom!

So you can fly my friend fly!
-
When you feel free and believe anything is possible, you finally get out of your own chuffing and do anything you want.
-
Being YOU is more than enough for the world.

I remember sitting in a bar in Vegas surrounded by these absolute glamour pusses, I felt small, insignificant and unattractive.

At that time in my life, I was riddled with insecurities I put other women on a pedestal and told myself I was not as good as them & never would be & that was something I would just have to accept.

I felt unhappy, inferior & stuck & my way of coping was to binge drink and to live a life of doing everything I could to be liked, in my mind if I couldn‚Äôt be like them then at least I could try and win them over so they liked me.

Fast forward to right now & now know that no one is better than me, I was never small or insignificant or unattractive that was just a story in my head & the more women I work with the clearer it becomes that... WE ALL HAVE THE SAME SHIT GOING ON! WE ARE ALL SO DIFFERENT BUT OMG ALL SO THE SAME!

My transformation from living my life as that woman to where I am today is why I became a coach.

I help women stuck feeling unhappy, unattractive & not good enough to start owning their confidence and to stop the body shaming & self-loathing they have struggled with maybe all their lives.
-
They get free from ;
üëâüèªfeeling stuck, lonely ashamed about their bodies
üëâüèªMissing out on dates/intimacy with their partners /holidays they dreamed of
üëâüèªthe funky food relationship
üëâüèªNot speaking their truth & being a priority in their own lives
-
How?
-
üëèüèª by identifying where they are now self-beliefs, nutrition, training lifestyle.
üôèüèª getting clarity on who they really WANT to be and what the current disconnect is.
üëèüèªThen taking action with a process where I give them the tools, support & accountability
üôèüèªWe continually evaluate, adjust & shift focuses as things change.
-
It won't happen overnight, it takes commitment & a willingness to get comfortable being uncomfortable.

But the transformation makes it all worthwhile.
-
‚ù§ From one woman to another, I hope you know you are not alone in your struggles and that NO ONE is perfect, no matter what picture they paint!

You have a right to be here, you can be happy and you can have everything you dream of.

Self boundaries are some of the most powerful things you can set yourself & honestly in my experience I find they make my life a little bit easier! I know where I stand with myself‚ù§Ô∏è But that‚Äôs enough from me over to  @therapyforwomen üëáüèª BOUNDARIES WITH YOURSELF

Rather than creating ‚Äúrules‚Äù for yourself, id recommend creating boundaries.

Boundaries can be molded, shifted and moved. Some are flexible, some are rigid. These are a list of some boundaries with yourself you want to put in place.

Please remember everyone is different. You will also need different things at different parts of your life and depending what‚Äôs going on.

For example, I have a very strict boundary that I don‚Äôt sleep with my phone in my room. It‚Äôs one of the best things I do for my mental health. However I was at the beach with friends this weekend and needed a way to wake up so I made an exception and had no shame or guilt around it.

Our lives are meant to shift and change as will our boundaries!

Are you going to implement any of these?

What boundaries do you have with yourself?

RELAX CHILLAX my friend... No one is happy all the time, not even Santa Claus!

You need times of sadness, anger, frustration to live the full human experience & learn shit! let yourself feel the uncomfortable feels!

And for the love of the season don‚Äôt judge or feel like a failure if you‚Äôre having a bad day or some downtimes, happiness isn‚Äôt a constant state!

But in reality, the majority of your life should bring more happiness & contentment vibes & feelings than anything because your health needs them!

The WHO states ‚ÄúHealth is a complete state of physical, mental and social well being, and not merely the absence of disease or infirmity‚Äù

Happiness & true life fulfilment aren't optional they're essential.

From my own experience & the Increasing research, the link between lack of social connections, support & loneliness is impacting our health negatively.

When you feel lonely and isolated you may turn to other things to try and fill the void (hello food and alcohol).
-
Here's the deal though, reading this post is not enough.üëèüèªYOU have to take action & start working them into your daily life.

You can‚Äôt sit back and expect connection,  happiness, fulfilment and joy to land in your lap and don‚Äôt expect it to be at the bottom of a bottle of wine or a box of crisps!

You will need to face up into your fear & get outside of your comfort zone to find you real connections, your tribe and to really discover what your happy truly is.

When you get there trust me you will be like ‚Äúoh now I see what life‚Äôs about‚Äù

This ageing process is one of the few things in life that is guaranteed and honestly, I am REALLY grateful for it.

I wouldn't want to be my younger self, I had no bloody clue who I was, what I wanted from life or what the hell was going on in my head!

I spent the majority of my time feeling confused about where I fitted & came to the conclusion that I didn‚Äôt think I did!
-
üëâüèªI partied A LOT using alcohol & drugs to deal with unhappiness &feelings I didn‚Äôt know how to deal with
üëâüèªI lived for validation so I spent my life crowd-pleasing
üëâüèªI spent a lot of time comparing my self to others
üëâüèªI made terrible choices when it came to men!
-
At age 41 I‚Äôm still a work in progress but feel younger and more driven to get what I want from life, to work on feeling the best I can both physically & mentally.

I am facing all my FEAR‚ÄôS and shit from my past that as it turns out to has been holding me back!
-
And I know it‚Äôs the work I‚Äôve done on my mind which has impacted my transformation the most.
-
Your mind has the power to help you age in reverse which if you think about it is so exciting because no one controls that but you.
-
So how YOU think and talk to yourself every day is what you need to get sorted, removing all of the daily self-imposed barriers...
üëâüèªif you don't believe you can stop feeling unhappy & isolated you won't.
üëâüèªif you don't believe you can get strong you won't.
üëâüèªif you don't believe you will meet your partner then you won't!
üëâüèªif you don't think you can do anything you want¬†then you won't.
-
With the wrong mindset, you will be trapped in the ageing process you actually FEAR the most.
-
Age is nothing but a number and YOU have the choice of how you want to let that number impact you.
-
Things do get harder but that doesn't mean impossible but you have to keep going, never giving up on you.
-
My intention to keep ageing in reverse to keep working towards and achieving my dreams until the day I die! #lifewithnoregrets

No one controls what goes down your gullet but you, you are your own responsibility and therefore you have to own any decisions you make.

But I know that shocked and slightly irritated face that happens when you say ‚Äúno thank you I don‚Äôt want a drink‚Äù

And at this time of year when the festive cheer is going strong, some people genuinely take this as a personal insult, like by saying no you‚Äôve totally ruined their Christmas!

And the problem is if you‚Äôre not really owning your decision and saying it with the utmost conviction, you will give the pusher the green light that you‚Äôre up for being persuaded.

And so the dance begins it can become awkward, annoying and seriously just boring.

You have the right to go out and enjoy your night just the way you want to and if someone is offended by your choices that‚Äôs their own shit!

You are not responsible for making someone else happy by joining them for an alcoholic beverage if you don‚Äôt want to!

You are only responsible for yourself and guaranteed the next day when you‚Äôre busy feeling annoyed beating yourself up because you didn‚Äôt do what you wanted, the drink pusher won‚Äôt be giving you a second thought.

Have you found yourself in a bit of a fitness rut?

In our latest episode of the Decades of Strength Podcast we share with you strategies that we‚Äôve personally used to get out of our deepest ruts.

1Ô∏è‚É£ Remember why you‚Äôre training in the first place. Check in with yourself on your goals & priorities. It‚Äôs ok if they change! Be clear in your mind as to what you want to achieve & why.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Rely on habits & dedication instead of motivation. The ‚Äúm‚Äù word gets thrown around a lot, but the harsh reality is you just won‚Äôt feel motivated all of the time. If not, rely on good habits (you are building those, right?) 3Ô∏è‚É£ Ensure accountability/tell others your goal: A friend to meet you at the gym, a coach, even an online friend/community to check in with and cheer you on.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Track your progress. Seeing how far you‚Äôve come as well as a path to where you want to go is a great strategy to prevent a rut. It keeps things fresh & interesting.
